1
00:00:22,464 --> 00:00:26,432
♪Should we forget yesterday's sorrows♪

2
00:00:26,432 --> 00:00:29,728
♪And the dazed confusion♪

3
00:00:30,976 --> 00:00:33,681
♪Should we let go of♪

4
00:00:33,681 --> 00:00:35,904
♪The stubborn madness♪

5
00:00:35,904 --> 00:00:39,072
♪And naive recklessness now♪

6
00:00:40,192 --> 00:00:43,840
♪Those years, those faces♪

7
00:00:44,992 --> 00:00:48,763
♪Those old scars we can't erase♪

8
00:00:49,824 --> 00:00:52,460
♪Tears streaming, facing the light♪

9
00:00:53,152 --> 00:00:57,594
♪Piercing the sorrow within♪

10
00:01:08,716 --> 00:01:12,736
♪The road ahead's long,
stumbling all the way♪

11
00:01:13,536 --> 00:01:18,076
♪The wounds we've borne
are medals hidden within♪

12
00:01:18,336 --> 00:01:22,391
♪Standing alone on an open plain♪

13
00:01:23,168 --> 00:01:26,851
♪We gaze at the stars♪

14
00:01:31,228 --> 00:01:34,816
=The Dream Maker=

15
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 21=

16
00:01:38,386 --> 00:01:41,276
(Today's quality, tomorrow's market)

17
00:01:42,546 --> 00:01:43,506
(Chunmei Printery)

18
00:01:47,954 --> 00:01:48,755
Well,

19
00:01:49,635 --> 00:01:50,555
we're at 100 now.

20
00:01:52,314 --> 00:01:54,915
It's okay. We're old acquaintances.
50 is fine.

21
00:01:55,354 --> 00:01:55,854
Hai,

22
00:01:56,995 --> 00:01:59,835
we help Ms. Gao move the goods.

23
00:02:00,514 --> 00:02:02,555
Just forget about the deputy mayor.

24
00:02:04,995 --> 00:02:05,495
Okay.

25
00:02:05,995 --> 00:02:08,034
50 will do, Xiaoyu.

26
00:02:08,434 --> 00:02:08,934
I'm leaving.

27
00:02:09,835 --> 00:02:11,594
Hai, why only 50?

28
00:02:11,955 --> 00:02:13,914
Can't we charge Ms. Gao's family
the normal rate?

29
00:02:14,314 --> 00:02:15,115
Yeah, Hai.

30
00:02:15,275 --> 00:02:16,874
Didn't we agree on the rules earlier?

31
00:02:17,194 --> 00:02:19,314
How can we keep working if you do this,

32
00:02:19,314 --> 00:02:19,814
right?

33
00:02:19,914 --> 00:02:20,795
- Yeah! Right?
- Exactly!

34
00:02:20,874 --> 00:02:21,395
Enough! Stop!

35
00:02:23,434 --> 00:02:23,934
See?

36
00:02:24,914 --> 00:02:27,194
You idiots have zero
situational awareness.

37
00:02:27,634 --> 00:02:28,194
Xiaoyu.

38
00:02:29,594 --> 00:02:30,355
Can you add a bit?

39
00:02:31,594 --> 00:02:33,874
We did set rules earlier.

40
00:02:36,474 --> 00:02:38,874
Wait. Yang Xiaohai, what do you mean?

41
00:02:39,194 --> 00:02:40,355
You saw it yourself.

42
00:02:40,754 --> 00:02:41,754
We set the rules.

43
00:02:42,034 --> 00:02:43,194
The current price,

44
00:02:43,914 --> 00:02:44,515
doesn't work.

45
00:02:45,154 --> 00:02:47,555
Yang Xiaohai, how could you do this?

46
00:02:48,075 --> 00:02:49,194
I kindly found you work,

47
00:02:49,314 --> 00:02:51,474
and you repay me
by demanding a higher price.

48
00:02:52,115 --> 00:02:53,555
I don't care about your rules.

49
00:02:53,754 --> 00:02:55,914
Take 50 or leave it. That's all I have.

50
00:02:59,434 --> 00:02:59,934
Okay.

51
00:03:00,555 --> 00:03:02,235
Then I'll go to Ms. Gao and the others.

52
00:03:02,955 --> 00:03:03,455
Hai.

53
00:03:05,634 --> 00:03:06,134
What?

54
00:03:06,275 --> 00:03:07,075
Yang Xiaohai!

55
00:03:07,594 --> 00:03:08,355
What are you doing?

56
00:03:08,874 --> 00:03:09,835
Who allow you to go in?

57
00:03:13,874 --> 00:03:15,154
Yang Xiaohai, what do you want?

58
00:03:18,795 --> 00:03:20,034
Who let you in?

59
00:03:20,634 --> 00:03:21,955
Mom, they're charging too much.

60
00:03:21,995 --> 00:03:23,075
50 yuan isn't even enough!

61
00:03:23,314 --> 00:03:24,675
Stop making such a racket.

62
00:03:25,194 --> 00:03:26,474
Can't handle this small matter?

63
00:03:29,154 --> 00:03:30,194
Come check these accounts.

64
00:03:38,555 --> 00:03:39,434
Start from here.

65
00:03:41,275 --> 00:03:42,194
Yes, up here.

66
00:03:42,515 --> 00:03:43,015
Okay.

67
00:03:46,194 --> 00:03:48,714
Yang Xiaohai! Long time no see.

68
00:03:50,555 --> 00:03:52,634
Seems you've landed big business lately.

69
00:03:58,314 --> 00:03:58,835
Ms. Gao,

70
00:03:59,914 --> 00:04:01,434
we helped move all your stuff.

71
00:04:03,075 --> 00:04:04,395
Charging market rates is fair,

72
00:04:05,355 --> 00:04:05,914
right?

73
00:04:06,314 --> 00:04:06,955
No problem.

74
00:04:07,474 --> 00:04:08,795
I understand market rules.

75
00:04:09,355 --> 00:04:12,355
But aren't you overcharging?

76
00:04:21,995 --> 00:04:22,555
Ms. Gao,

77
00:04:23,274 --> 00:04:24,915
during the typhoon,

78
00:04:25,235 --> 00:04:27,834
our whole crew rushed
to the dock to help you.

79
00:04:28,514 --> 00:04:30,035
True, we moved the machinery

80
00:04:30,274 --> 00:04:31,954
after the typhoon hit.

81
00:04:32,274 --> 00:04:34,874
And today, we worked hard too,

82
00:04:35,434 --> 00:04:37,434
unloading this entire truck.

83
00:04:37,754 --> 00:04:38,874
Charging this much

84
00:04:40,115 --> 00:04:41,035
is reasonable, right?

85
00:04:41,995 --> 00:04:43,415
It is indeed.

86
00:04:44,155 --> 00:04:46,915
You did help me greatly
at the dock that day.

87
00:04:47,434 --> 00:04:48,754
I remember you well.

88
00:04:48,754 --> 00:04:50,595
A loyal and righteous young man.

89
00:04:51,235 --> 00:04:53,274
But why act like this today?

90
00:04:54,194 --> 00:04:54,694
Come on.

91
00:04:55,834 --> 00:04:57,834
Xuemei, please review these accounts.

92
00:04:57,995 --> 00:04:59,995
Okay. I'll review them properly.

93
00:05:03,995 --> 00:05:05,855
So you're talking about favors today?

94
00:05:05,915 --> 00:05:06,754
Forget business.

95
00:05:07,274 --> 00:05:08,434
No matter how much you moved,

96
00:05:08,475 --> 00:05:09,795
I'll pay you.

97
00:05:10,355 --> 00:05:10,995
Name your price.

98
00:05:18,314 --> 00:05:18,834
Name it.

99
00:05:24,035 --> 00:05:25,115
Too shy to say it?

100
00:05:25,754 --> 00:05:26,456
How about this?

101
00:05:27,074 --> 00:05:28,514
Take as much as you want from there.

102
00:05:28,874 --> 00:05:29,995
Keep whatever you take.

103
00:05:30,475 --> 00:05:32,355
Consider it the Money God's gift.

104
00:05:54,434 --> 00:05:56,314
No need to feel awkward.

105
00:05:57,954 --> 00:05:58,555
No.

106
00:05:58,874 --> 00:06:00,434
But I'm telling you, Yang Xiaohai.

107
00:06:00,954 --> 00:06:02,634
However much you take,

108
00:06:03,555 --> 00:06:04,795
it's not earned by labor.

109
00:06:07,074 --> 00:06:08,834
It's traded on personal favors.

110
00:06:09,155 --> 00:06:09,834
Understand?

111
00:06:20,475 --> 00:06:21,675
I'll leave now.

112
00:06:33,155 --> 00:06:36,115
I need to see Mr. Zheng tomorrow
to resolve this.

113
00:06:40,675 --> 00:06:42,434
These kids are getting out of hand!

114
00:06:43,954 --> 00:06:46,355
Has everyone besides Xuemei
faced this issue?

115
00:06:46,434 --> 00:06:47,514
- Yeah, Mr. Zheng.
- Yes.

116
00:06:47,514 --> 00:06:48,475
Here are the receipts.

117
00:06:49,274 --> 00:06:49,774
Tan.

118
00:06:50,715 --> 00:06:51,215
Tan.

119
00:06:51,754 --> 00:06:52,995
(Secretary's Office)
What did you city inspectors do?

120
00:06:53,235 --> 00:06:53,735
No.

121
00:06:53,855 --> 00:06:54,355
Mr. Zheng.

122
00:06:54,355 --> 00:06:55,074
What did you do?

123
00:06:55,155 --> 00:06:56,754
This isn't Mr. Tan's fault.

124
00:06:56,995 --> 00:06:57,995
After the typhoon,

125
00:06:57,995 --> 00:06:58,995
manpower was needed.

126
00:06:59,074 --> 00:07:00,475
Besides Binhai Road, Mr. Tan

127
00:07:00,475 --> 00:07:01,595
had a lot on his plate.

128
00:07:02,074 --> 00:07:03,834
Yang Xiaohai and his group went too far.

129
00:07:04,514 --> 00:07:05,634
Of course, I'm at fault too.

130
00:07:05,915 --> 00:07:07,995
I knew about their high-priced moving.

131
00:07:08,394 --> 00:07:10,475
They helped me during the typhoon,

132
00:07:10,795 --> 00:07:12,475
so I thought I'd just let it be high.

133
00:07:12,514 --> 00:07:13,355
I didn't think much.

134
00:07:13,754 --> 00:07:14,394
I never expected

135
00:07:15,235 --> 00:07:17,035
it would fuel their greed. You know.

136
00:07:17,035 --> 00:07:17,535
Okay.

137
00:07:18,235 --> 00:07:19,394
You cared about Yang Xiaohai.

138
00:07:19,915 --> 00:07:20,715
What about others?

139
00:07:21,394 --> 00:07:22,680
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

140
00:07:25,754 --> 00:07:27,160
Tan, I'm asking you.

141
00:07:27,874 --> 00:07:29,995
Mr. Zheng, well...

142
00:07:30,355 --> 00:07:31,595
Actually, I investigated this.

143
00:07:31,595 --> 00:07:34,194
It's not just
Yang Xiaohai's problem alone.

144
00:07:34,314 --> 00:07:35,314
Then whose problem is it?

145
00:07:37,355 --> 00:07:39,394
There's someone else leading them.

146
00:07:39,715 --> 00:07:40,274
Who?

147
00:07:42,194 --> 00:07:44,715
Mr. Zheng, look, I think
you should calm down first, okay?

148
00:07:44,874 --> 00:07:45,434
Calm down.

149
00:07:45,434 --> 00:07:46,274
Listen. Maybe

150
00:07:46,274 --> 00:07:47,595
you should talk to Desheng?

151
00:07:47,795 --> 00:07:48,954
How is he involved?

152
00:07:52,155 --> 00:07:52,874
What do you mean?

153
00:07:55,715 --> 00:07:56,555
Are you saying

154
00:07:57,274 --> 00:07:59,754
it's my nephew, Zheng Zhiqiang, right?

155
00:08:06,834 --> 00:08:07,715
City inspectors!

156
00:08:08,314 --> 00:08:09,634
Grab your gear if you're done.

157
00:08:09,675 --> 00:08:11,314
If not, eat faster. We need to patrol.

158
00:08:11,675 --> 00:08:12,434
Come on.

159
00:08:12,675 --> 00:08:13,514
Hurry up! Assemble!

160
00:08:13,555 --> 00:08:14,434
Assemble!

161
00:08:18,874 --> 00:08:21,115
Mr. Tan, they haven't
finished eating yet.

162
00:08:21,194 --> 00:08:22,434
Why patrol now?

163
00:08:22,874 --> 00:08:23,795
Forced moving.

164
00:08:23,954 --> 00:08:25,834
These guys run away when you show up.

165
00:08:25,915 --> 00:08:27,754
And they're back
once you leave. Annoying.

166
00:08:28,355 --> 00:08:29,874
Finished eating? Hurry up.

167
00:08:30,795 --> 00:08:31,954
Assemble under the bike shed.

168
00:08:32,355 --> 00:08:32,855
You eat.

169
00:08:32,874 --> 00:08:33,514
- Okay.
- You eat.

170
00:08:37,234 --> 00:08:41,554
(Grand Piano)

171
00:08:45,154 --> 00:08:46,914
Drive slower.

172
00:08:47,274 --> 00:08:49,075
Don't you know this piano is expensive?

173
00:08:50,715 --> 00:08:51,634
Okay, boss.

174
00:08:56,154 --> 00:08:58,195
Do you think we'll run
into those people today?

175
00:08:58,475 --> 00:08:59,355
Who?

176
00:09:00,075 --> 00:09:01,235
Xiaohai and his crew.

177
00:09:03,195 --> 00:09:03,835
No.

178
00:09:05,115 --> 00:09:06,315
We're not that unlucky.

179
00:09:06,914 --> 00:09:09,034
How would they know
where I'm coming back from?

180
00:09:09,835 --> 00:09:11,874
They say they're everywhere now.

181
00:09:11,995 --> 00:09:12,914
Elusive.

182
00:09:13,394 --> 00:09:14,355
All over the place.

183
00:09:16,154 --> 00:09:17,195
It's fine.

184
00:09:22,394 --> 00:09:23,034
Wake up!

185
00:09:28,850 --> 00:09:30,328
Oh, my!

186
00:09:46,235 --> 00:09:48,504
What are you doing
blocking the road here?

187
00:09:49,245 --> 00:09:51,794
Mr. Dog, the road ahead is too bumpy.

188
00:09:52,355 --> 00:09:54,835
The piano is so valuable.
What if it gets damaged?

189
00:09:55,075 --> 00:09:56,794
We'll help you carry it in.

190
00:09:56,995 --> 00:09:58,595
Let us see it too.

191
00:09:58,715 --> 00:10:00,034
Just tell me how much you want.

192
00:10:00,235 --> 00:10:00,735
Mr. Dog,

193
00:10:01,034 --> 00:10:02,634
the fish that day was pretty pricey.

194
00:10:03,435 --> 00:10:03,955
Qiang,

195
00:10:04,754 --> 00:10:06,874
how much did that meal cost us again?

196
00:10:07,554 --> 00:10:09,315
Seems like over 1,000.

197
00:10:10,075 --> 00:10:11,394
You see, a piano is so heavy.

198
00:10:11,554 --> 00:10:13,435
It can't be cheaper
than that meal, right?

199
00:10:13,435 --> 00:10:15,315
Why don't you just rob me?

200
00:10:15,315 --> 00:10:16,754
You can't say that, Mr. Dog.

201
00:10:16,914 --> 00:10:18,154
This isn't robbery.

202
00:10:18,235 --> 00:10:19,794
We're helping you move your stuff.

203
00:10:20,075 --> 00:10:21,754
And we're just trying to make a living.

204
00:10:22,674 --> 00:10:23,174
Well...

205
00:10:23,195 --> 00:10:25,174
Hai, lunchtime?

206
00:10:27,115 --> 00:10:27,754
Lunchtime!

207
00:10:28,154 --> 00:10:29,355
- Lunchtime!
- Lunchtime!

208
00:10:29,455 --> 00:10:29,955
Let's go!

209
00:10:29,955 --> 00:10:32,115
Bao, treat Mr. Dog to something nice.

210
00:10:32,435 --> 00:10:32,955
Got it.

211
00:10:33,235 --> 00:10:33,914
Gently!

212
00:10:35,154 --> 00:10:36,235
Get down!

213
00:10:36,674 --> 00:10:37,355
You! Get down!

214
00:10:38,235 --> 00:10:38,835
My treat!

215
00:10:38,995 --> 00:10:40,274
What treat?

216
00:10:40,514 --> 00:10:42,595
Yes! Untie the ropes!

217
00:10:44,394 --> 00:10:45,754
Open the gate.

218
00:10:46,715 --> 00:10:47,215
Unload.

219
00:10:47,274 --> 00:10:47,995
Unload the piano.

220
00:10:49,274 --> 00:10:49,774
Stop.

221
00:10:49,914 --> 00:10:50,414
Move it.

222
00:10:51,235 --> 00:10:52,075
Why hold me back?

223
00:10:52,075 --> 00:10:55,034
I don't want to eat.
I don't want noodles.

224
00:10:55,075 --> 00:10:56,874
I'm not hungry. Why would I eat noodles?

225
00:10:58,315 --> 00:10:58,955
Slow down.

226
00:10:59,674 --> 00:11:01,235
People below, move!

227
00:11:01,715 --> 00:11:02,794
One, two...

228
00:11:04,955 --> 00:11:05,455
What now?

229
00:11:06,034 --> 00:11:07,274
Dog, the restaurant doesn't...

230
00:11:11,315 --> 00:11:12,514
Isn't the piano made of steel?

231
00:11:13,835 --> 00:11:14,715
Forget it. Move it.

232
00:11:14,735 --> 00:11:15,235
Hurry! Go!

233
00:11:15,235 --> 00:11:15,914
As Qiang says,

234
00:11:16,154 --> 00:11:16,715
let's move it.

235
00:11:17,475 --> 00:11:19,115
Let go of me!

236
00:11:24,914 --> 00:11:26,435
I'll run you over!

237
00:11:26,674 --> 00:11:28,554
What are you spouting?
Running people over?

238
00:11:30,195 --> 00:11:31,355
Close it properly. Quick!

239
00:11:36,394 --> 00:11:37,154
Get out of the way!

240
00:11:38,995 --> 00:11:40,514
Dog, have you lost your mind?

241
00:11:47,115 --> 00:11:47,615
Move!

242
00:12:04,274 --> 00:12:04,955
Murder!

243
00:12:05,195 --> 00:12:05,695
Murder!

244
00:12:06,355 --> 00:12:07,315
How could you hit us?

245
00:12:07,634 --> 00:12:08,134
Go!

246
00:12:08,475 --> 00:12:08,975
Get them!

247
00:12:16,874 --> 00:12:18,394
Once it's dirty, it's hard to fix!

248
00:12:35,698 --> 00:12:39,090
(Haoyue Bridge)

249
00:12:53,154 --> 00:12:55,235
Mr. Zheng, where are you rushing off to?

250
00:12:55,554 --> 00:12:57,394
Zhiqiang is using my name
to force relocations.

251
00:12:57,595 --> 00:12:58,355
I'll deal with him.

252
00:12:58,554 --> 00:12:59,235
Zhiqiang?

253
00:13:00,034 --> 00:13:00,995
Did you check it out?

254
00:13:01,394 --> 00:13:02,914
Mr. Zheng, Ms. Li, it's bad!

255
00:13:03,995 --> 00:13:04,874
Fight on Fuyu Road!

256
00:13:10,835 --> 00:13:11,394
Stop fighting!

257
00:13:12,274 --> 00:13:12,835
Stop!

258
00:13:13,154 --> 00:13:13,674
Stop!

259
00:13:13,754 --> 00:13:14,254
Stop it!

260
00:13:14,315 --> 00:13:15,115
Enough fighting!

261
00:13:15,835 --> 00:13:16,794
Don't fight!

262
00:13:17,274 --> 00:13:17,874
Don't fight!

263
00:13:18,315 --> 00:13:18,995
Stop hitting!

264
00:13:19,154 --> 00:13:19,654
Go!

265
00:13:19,874 --> 00:13:20,475
No violence!

266
00:13:20,955 --> 00:13:21,455
Come here!

267
00:13:22,715 --> 00:13:23,914
Don't fight!

268
00:13:25,075 --> 00:13:26,715
Stop fighting! It's crazy!

269
00:13:59,475 --> 00:14:00,514
So what if you're rich?

270
00:14:02,715 --> 00:14:03,674
So what if you're rich?

271
00:14:07,914 --> 00:14:08,554
Yang Xiaohai!

272
00:14:09,154 --> 00:14:09,720
What is this?

273
00:14:23,235 --> 00:14:25,674
Hit him! If you dare hit him,
do it in front of me.

274
00:14:26,514 --> 00:14:29,075
Don't provoke him.
He really will hit me!

275
00:14:29,595 --> 00:14:32,115
Does your grandma know
you're fighting out here?

276
00:14:37,435 --> 00:14:38,034
Stop fighting!

277
00:14:38,514 --> 00:14:39,014
Ge away!

278
00:14:39,235 --> 00:14:40,034
No more fighting!

279
00:14:41,394 --> 00:14:43,435
Ms. Li, hurry. Save me!

280
00:14:43,835 --> 00:14:45,475
They beat me so badly I can't breathe.

281
00:14:45,914 --> 00:14:46,595
I'm dying.

282
00:14:46,595 --> 00:14:48,235
Fatty, what nonsense are you spouting?

283
00:14:48,235 --> 00:14:49,674
Look! Look at them!

